’Ů@4771e7e88642e5547870d942f46fe5d1a43dfbaf88d36cec09403af3229e7e0aÚTitle: title: collect
Path: Examples
Content:
Use the second value in the stream.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [1 2 3] | collect { |x| $x.1 }
2

```
Read and write to the same file.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> open file.txt | collect | save -f file.txt


```
’Ů@edd3276cc4fa6014b3ddd1fdd8e927b0de8876931eeccba90ecfbae96ba25a87ŮňTitle: title: collect
Path: Notes
Content:
If provided, run a closure with the collected value as input.
The entire stream will be collected into one value in memory, so if the stream

is particularly large, this can cause high memory usage.
